events.name: LSU Tigers at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Jarrett Lee threw two touchdown passes, and Spencer Ware caught one and ran for another score as No. 1 LSU stayed unbeaten with another rout, 38-7 against Tennessee on Saturday.

events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Trent Richardson rushed for 183 yards and a career-high four touchdowns and No. 2 Alabama's defense smothered foundering Mississippi in a 52-7 win on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Richardson runs wild as Alabama routs Ole Miss

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at Kansas Jayhawks

headlines.description: No. 3 Oklahoma 47, Kansas 17
headlines.shortLinkText: Broyles sets record; Oklahoma rolls Kansas

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Quarterback Russell Wilson added a new chapter to his brief-but-growing legend, making a touchdown catch on a trick play as No. 4 Wisconsin routed Indiana 59-7 on Saturday.

events.name: Boise State Broncos at Colorado State Rams

headlines.description: Boise State routed Colorado State 63-13 in their Mountain West debut Saturday behind huge games from quarterback Kellen Moore, tailback Doug Martin and wide receiver Tyler Shoemaker.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boise State clobbers Colorado St. in MWC debut

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Jeremy Smith ran for 140 yards and scored on two long touchdown runs and No. 6 Oklahoma State beat No. 22 Texas 38-26 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith's 2 rushing TDs carry Okla. St. by Texas

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Andrew Luck threw two third-quarter touchdown passes to Levine Toilolo as No. 7 Stanford beat Washington State 44-14 Saturday to extend the nation's longest winning streak to a school record 14 consecutive games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stanford strolls past Wazzou to win 14th straight

events.name: Clemson Tigers at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd threw four touchdown passes, freshman Sammy and No. 8 Clemson rallied from an 18-point deficit against Maryland to remain unbeaten with a 56-45 victory Saturday night.

events.name: Arizona State Sun Devils at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: No. 9 Oregon 41, No. 18 Arizona St. 27

events.name: Michigan Wolverines at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Keshawn Martin scored twice in the third quarter on similar lunges to the end zone, and No. 23 Michigan State held off Denard Robinson and No. 11 Michigan 28-14 on Saturday for its fourth straight victory over the Wolverines.

events.name: Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at Virginia Cavaliers

headlines.description: Perry Jones ran for 149 of Virginia's 272 yards on the ground and the Cavaliers beat No. 12 Georgia Tech at its own game, 24-21, on Saturday night.

events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Alshon Jeffrey caught a 4-yard touchdown pass from Connor Shaw with 3:50 left in the fourth quarter and No. 15 South Carolina rallied to beat Mississippi State 14-12 on Saturday.

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: Dan Herron, who hadn't played since the Sugar Bowl in January because of NCAA suspensions, ran for 114 yards and a touchdown in his return Saturday to lead Ohio State past No. 16 Illinois, 17-7.

events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Collin Klein ran for three touchdowns and threw for another as No. 17 Kansas State came from behind to beat Texas Tech 41-34 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: K-State comes back on Tx. Tech, moves to 6-0

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Logan Thomas rushed for two touchdowns and passed for two more to lead No. 19 Virginia Tech past Wake Forest 38-17 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Va. Tech rallies from early hole to sink Wake

events.name: Baylor Bears at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Ryan Tannehill threw for 415 yards and a career-high six touchdowns and Ryan Swope caught four of them to lead No. 21 Texas A&M to a 55-28 win over No. 20 Baylor on Saturday.

events.name: Florida Gators at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Onterio McCalebb opened the fourth quarter with a 14-yard touchdown run, Ikeem Means recovered a muffed punt late and No. 24 Auburn beat Florida 17-6 in a defensive game that saw seven players take snaps at quarterback.
headlines.shortLinkText: Auburn tops Florida as both struggle offensively

events.name: Purdue Boilermakers at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: Silas Redd ran for 131 yards and a touchdown and Penn State took advantage of Purdue's special teams miscues to hold on Saturday for a 23-18 win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penn St. leans on Redd, Purdue's mistakes

events.name: Utah Utes at Pittsburgh Panthers

headlines.description: John White ran for 171 yards and Coleman Petersen kicked four field goals in the tricky Heinz Field winds to lead Utah by reeling Pittsburgh 26-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah's Petersen manages 4 FGs in gusting wind

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Isaiah Pead made two quick cutbacks and ran 50 yard for the go-ahead touchdown in the fourth quarter Saturday, rallying Cincinnati to a 25-16 victory over Louisville in the Big East opener for both teams at Paul Brown Stadium.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cincy scoots past Louisville with late touchdown
